d the random forest and neural network models the most. Their\naccuracy tended to converge toward deviation values close to 1% from a number\nof dwell positions greater than 100. Conclusions: In performing HDR\nbrachytherapy dose measurements with an optimized mPSD system, ML algorithms\nare good alternatives for precise dose reporting and treatment assessment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 1 May 2020 14:28:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-04"}
